Problem

<= /span>

The checkout JavaScript throws a R= eferenceError when it tries to read the braintree global, which stops the PayPal/Braintre= e initialization. As a result PayPal and PayPal Credit buttons may not appe= ar or be usable on checkout pages. The failure is coming from the site's ch= eckout JS file (main-= checkout-hub.js).

Impact

The user-visible eff= ect is that PayPal and PayPal Credit payment options may be missing or unre= sponsive on checkout pages (observed on checkout/hub pages). Customers can = still often use other payment methods, but anyone trying to pay with PayPal= /Braintree will not be able to start that flow. The problem appears frequen= tly on mobile Safari/WebView environments, so a subset of customers (notabl= y mobile users) are affected.
